<TEXT>
thousands of employees of local kaiser 
permanente hospitals and medical offices pledged to go on strike 
monday after a weekend negotiating session failed to resolve a 
labor dispute officials said sunday 
the union has issued a strike alert for one minute after 
midnight said janice seib a spokeswoman for kaiser permanente 
the nations oldest and largest health maintenance organization 
the service employees union representing 11000 hospital workers 
rejected kaisers threeyear 44million contract and a federally 
mediated session produced no new resolutions 
the union includes licensed vocational nurses clerks house 
keepers and radiology technicians at seven of the pasadenabased 
kaiser permanente medical centers and more than 40 satellite 
medical offices in los angeles and orange counties 
kaiser will draw additional workers from other kaiser facilities 
in san bernardino riverside and san diego counties that are 
unaffected by the strike called by clerical technical and service 
employees seib said 
weve already been reducing the number of patients in our 
hospitals from 40 to 60 percent seib said adding officials have 
transferred some patients and postponed nonemergency surgeries and 
elective surgeries 
a sixhour negotiating session with representatives from service 
employees international union local 399 ended saturday without an 
agreement seib said 
the feeling is that weve presented the union with an 
extremely fair contract that guarantees theyll always be paid 4 
percent higher than any other facility in the area seib said 
the contract offer included a 5 percent to 6 percent raise in 
the first year and a 3 percent to 5 percent raise during the second 
and third year the offer was approved by the union negotiating 
team on thursday 
the next day some 5000 workers less than half of the union 
membership voted to rejected the contract by a more than 
twotoone ratio said tom ramsay a union spokesman 
kaiser employees accepted a wage freeze three years ago and have 
stood by the company during its nine years of financial difficulty 
ramsay said 
now that kaiser is back on their feet and prospering 
employees expected some recognition and didnt get that and they 
were very angry ramsay said 
the hospitals affected by the labor dispute are located in los 
angeles west los angeles panorama city woodland hills harbor 
city bellflower and anaheim said seib 
</TEXT>
