a soviet defector whose family 
joined him in the united states last year after a 9year struggle 
allegedly shot and killed his wife and one daughter and wounded 
another daughter police said saturday 
valentin bereza 58 fled to tennessee after the shootings 
thursday night and surrendered saturday morning to police in 
nashville police said nashville homicide detective walter keeler 
jr said bereza was being held for florida police on a fugitive 
warrant 
bereza is charged with the premeditated shooting deaths of his 
wife raisa bereza 53 and daughter elena 30 as well as the 
premeditated attempted murder of his second daughter tonya 17 
the sheriffs office in lee county fla said saturday 
officers in north fort myers said raisa and elena bereza died of 
gunshots to the head from a largecaliber handgun tonya bereza was 
in fair condition in a hospital recovering from a gunshot to the 
face 
according to tonya her father put on his best suit before 
announcing that he was unhappy with elenas behavior the 
statement said without elaboration 
he gathered his family around the dinner table and told them 
im leaving and im going to kill you now lee county sheriffs 
spokesman robert graziano said then he pulled out a gun and 
started shooting 
tonya fled the house as bereza went into another room to reload 
the gun the sheriffs office said 
bereza a civil engineer defected from the ukraine in the 
soviet union in july 1980 and had lived in fort myers for about 
three years police said with help from the us government elena 
was able to emigrate last may and raisa and tonya followed in 
september 
the state department had been notified after the shooting 
thursday in case he tried to leave the country 
