<TEXT>
air routes between nepals capital of katmandu 
and the tibetan capital of lhasa have been reopened more than a 
year after being suspended because of antichinese turmoil in 
lhasa a news agency reported 
the crosshimalayan international route was inaugurated in 1987 
but closed after violent clashes between tibetans seeking 
independence from china and security forces led to the declaration 
of martial law in lhasa last march 8 
china has since banned almost all visits by foreign diplomats 
journalists and tourists not traveling in an organized tour it now 
allows tour groups of three or more people to travel to lhasa but 
restricts where they can stay and what they can see 
chinas xinhua news agency said saturday that a royal nepal 
airlines boeing 707 will fly one way from katmandu to lhasa every 
wednesday from april 25 and an air china boeing 707 will make the 
return trip every saturday 
