vento 21 an important witness in the slaying backed out of a 
deal and decided to face seconddegree murder charges rather than 
testify against his friends 
seven other young white men from bensonhurst have been charged 
in the aug 23 slaying of yusuf hawkins a black 16yearold who 
was shot after he went with three friends into the largely italian 
neighborhood in south brooklyn to look at a used car 
 
judge thaddeus owens ruled last week that alleged triggerman 
joseph fama 19 and alleged ringleader keith mondello 20 would 
be the first to stand trial prosecutors said jury selection 
begins monday 
both men are charged with two counts of murder and face 25 years 
to life in prison if convicted five of the others have been 
charged with murder and other crimes and the sixth with assault 
brooklyn district attorney charles j hynes says he is baffled 
by mcintyres resignation and regrets ventos change of heart but 
insists hes confident he has a case he can win 
ventos unexpected defection led prosecutors to seek and get a 
onemonth delay in the start of the trials 
on monday the judge plans to speed the proceedings by 
impaneling two juries the panels will sit side by side in the 
courtroom with one deciding the fate of fama and the other 
considering the case of mondello 
there may be as many as six trials defense lawyers and 
prosecutors say 
the murder labeled racial from the outset by police and 
prosecutors sparked a furor across the city it is widely viewed 
as the most serious racial incident in the city since a december 
1986 attack in new yorks howard beach neighborhood in which a 
black man chased by a gang of whites ran onto a highway and was 
struck and killed by car 
the bensonhurst killing apparently was ignited by a dispute 
between mondello and a former girlfriend gina feliciano as word 
raced through the neighborhood that miss feliciano had invited a 
group of black and hispanic friends to her 18th birthday party 
mondello allegedly recruited some of his friends to take on what 
they saw as intruders on their turf 
the gang of some 30 whites many armed with baseball bats 
mistook hawkins and his three teenage friends all of them black 
as the expected outsiders and set upon them 
as the gang surrounded the four youths fama allegedly stepped 
in with his gun and fired four shots three of which struck hawkins 
and killed him 
the mob scattered when the shots were fired and hawkins 
companions who are expected to testify at the trials were not 
hurt 
