in the first serious hurdle to collors 2weekold 
administration congress will grapple with the 26 measures that 
have paralyzed brazils economy and raised fears of social 
instability lawmakers have two weeks to scrap or alter the plan 
collor brazils first popularly elected leader since 1960 
decreed the countrys fifth and most radical austerity package 
march 16 to curb 4853 percent annual inflation and jump start 
brazils stagnant economy 
but the plan which freezes savings accounts above 1200 for 
18 months severely tightens the money supply raises taxes and 
utility rates and slashes government spending has run into 
mounting opposition 
brazils communist party the leftist workers party and the 
centerleft democratic labor party have condemned the package in 
addition five centrist parties holding a solid majority of about 
400 votes in the 570member congress have demanded substantial 
changes 
