controversial measures 
voting on the heart of the plan is expected to be held later in 
the week or early next week 
under pressure from labor unions businessmen and voters party 
leaders have expressed support for increasing the limit of bank 
withdrawals the freeze has caused a brutal shortage of currency 
causing consumer demand to drop near zero and triggering massive 
layoffs 
unions estimate that more than 200000 brazilians have lost 
their jobs since the plan was implemented hardest hit were 
construction and auto industry workers including 19000 laid off 
in southern parana state and 11000 in rio de janeiro 
