ahimeir noted that shamir was now acting as defense minister a 
post he took over after rabins resignation from the cabinet on 
march 13 during the crisis that led to the government collapse 
if there were artificial delays until now they will be 
removed ahimeir said in a telephone interview ahimeir said the 
settlements were authorized by a cabinet decision more than a year 
ago 
labor legislator avraham burg said shamir also wanted to 
confiscate additional land for settlements and enlarge the present 
jewish enclaves around hebron where clashes have occurred between 
settlers and palestinians 
burg told the associated press that shamirs plans were in line 
with the likud philosphy of not giving up any land in the occupied 
territories even in exchange for peace 
part of the plan is to kill the peace process he said 
since capturing the west bank and gaza during the 1967 middle 
east war israel has built 143 settlements that are home to 75000 
jews about 17 million palestinians live in the occupied lands 
an additional 120000 israelis have been moved into 
neighborhoods built in the israeliannexed sector of jerusalem 
where 140000 palestinians live 
three settlements have been opened since shamir was reelected 
premier in november 1988 these are ofarim and tsoref started may 
10 in the west bank and kfar darom started about the same time in 
gaza 
five others agreed on as a compromise between shamir and peres 
when they formed their coalition government have not been built 
and their names and sites have not been disclosed 
ahimeir confirmed a radio report that shamir has named michael 
dekel a veteran likud activist and former deputy defense minister 
to be in charge of building the new settlements 
the radio said dekel still needs permits from the military 
government in the occupied teritories and the justice ministry 
which controls land purchases in the past some settlements have 
been started by putting up fences and moving in mobile homes 
peres meanwhile was seeking to break a 6060 deadlock with 
